caption: Sable kitchen has some of the best unique concoctions! 100% a must visit.

Great food! Loved the ambience,  right down to the unassuming storefront and especially the unique front door. I had the biscuits and gravy which was so delicious and the home fried potatoes are the best!

A slice of home spun country in the heart of the city! Chicago's little secret you want to tell everyone about.  French toast is thick and tastes amazing! CA omelet was savory.  2nd time here. Will DEFINITELY come again!
The food is amazing, the alcohol choices are unique.
Good food and reasonable prices

Oh man, how did this place go from an awesome cool stylish restaurant to sort of a weird hotel bar. It’s kind of a step up from a sports bar now.  I’m so sad because the cocktails here used to be delicious and the food options used to be amazing. I can remember having brunch here and having fantastic dishes, this time it was a really limited menu and very very unimpressive
Dry gin martini. I will always come back to this bar. They make the best cocktails. Awesome customer service. Great hotel! So far no complaints!

Innovative cocktails in beautiful modern location; however, I wish there had been some "normal" options for drinks especially for someone who is relatively unversed in craft cocktails. The service was friendly but not overly attentive.
Excellent, especially for a hotel bar / restaurant
Delicious and delicate food.

Food was excellent. I casually mentioned that I was planning to split a meal with someone, and when the food came, the meal was split onto two plates! Roger was our waiter. Super nice guy. Exceptional service overall! Would give an extra star if possible.
I’ve been here a Handel full of times. Always delicious. Must try the breakfast!
Presentation of food was good. Food was awesome.
(Translated by Google) Amazing!  (Original) Alucinante!

I cannot recommend this place enough. I was hesitant because it was attached to a hotel but it was the highlight of my trip. We didn't eat but I did try out several cocktails. When I couldn't make up my mind the bartender asked for my preferences and made me a random ridiculously delicious off the menu cocktail. The service was great as was the waitstaff. I would definitely go back.
The bartenders were great!  Try one of their custom designed drinks while you are there.

Amazing selection of drinks, good food and attentive staff.  One of the top hotel bars in America and definitely one of our favorites in Chicago.  Take some time to read thru the extensive menu and spoil yourself with something creative.  With the upscale offerings comes an upscale price, but it's worth it.
Nice place for a drink
Roger the bartender made the perfect drink for me. He knows how to make people feel welcome & at home. What a great way to start the day in Chicago!
Consistently one of the best cocktail bars in Chicago.  A bit pricey but nothing out of the ordinary for the location.
Always solid food.
Nice, modern.

Since I was a wee one my family fed me Bourbon. Once I was of age I looked for bars that knew their whiskeys and bourbons. This joint is full of knowledgeable bar staff and generous one ounce pours that allow self education. This here southern boy hits Chicago 3-5 times a year. I will not miss this stop in the future! AND, the food rocks too! Best Happy Hour pricing around.

Went for happy hour (M-F, 4-6pm) and the drink selection is pretty good.  All the classic staple cocktails.  There was some food on happy hour special too, but we weren't hungry so didn't get anything (believe the deviled eggs are one of their specialties).  Would definitely come back again for happy hour.

I cannot recommend this place enough. I was hesitant because it was attached to a hotel but it was the highlight of my trip. We didn't eat but I did try out several cocktails. When I couldn't make up my mind the bartender asked for my preferences and made me a random ridiculously delicious off the menu cocktail. The service was great as was the waitstaff. I would definitely go back.

Very disappointed! We have a large number of family and friends in town for wedding. All staying at the Palomar. Everyone meets after the rehearsal dinner for a drink at the Sable. Uncle of the bride celebrating 50th birthday! Oh sorry no cake allowed! You can sing and look at the cake but you can’t eat it in our bar where you and your party are spending hundreds if not more on drinks! And by the way you can’t eat the M&Ms either that came from the mini bar in your room in the very same hotel!! Wait staff stalks you all night to make sure you don’t use one of their forks to sneak some of that cake!  You must be kidding me. I’ll never return here again!
Creative cocktails, good food, attentive service.

This is a really great place.  The ambiance and decor is relaxed with a nice upscale feel.  The food is fantastic and the staff is friendly.  They have a nice cocktail and spirit selection.  We stopped here for a late lunch and ordered a few sharables.  Everything was wonderful.  The calabrian toast (on the weekend afternoon menu) was absolutely amazing.  We also ordered the fries, which were good but not great, although the garlic aioli made them much better.  I would definitely go back the next time I'm in the city.  For couple cocktails and some small plates, this place was perfect.

This is not known for breakfast so it isn't crowded. It is a great spot for breakfast. Private, good service and the food is excellent. Because it is relatively empty, the service shines. All of the menu options are fresh and delicious. I'd come back here for breakfast in a minute. As a guest I was introduced to Sable as my dining option. I was impressed by the quality of the meals I received and must recommend the oatmeal, kale caser salad, and burger (served with 7 min egg) YUM.
Huge menu, young staff not very knowledgeable.

Really amazing and creatively constructed cocktails at this bar! Plus, the food is quite good, as well. It’s attached to a Kimpton hotel property; we enjoyed our breakfasts there, in the mornings, during our stay. It’s not low-priced, but it lives up to its standards. Really RECOMMEND this bar and experience!

Party of 5 on a Friday around 9 pm. This place is small but we were able to combine two tables to fit us all. The waiter was really friendly and helpful in deciding what to order. The Sable burger is good and the drinks are yummy!

Proper cheese and charcuterie plate, they know what they're doing. Also awesome presentation of themed drinks and good beer selection, definitely a great place to pause in the city and escape some of the more packed spots.
Not a lot of brunch options but the staff is really good.

Always solid cocktails at this bar. We were staying in the polamar so this place was great for a night cap. They have a great cocktail list. The bartender was friendly and quick. Ice cubes were nice and clear. The old fashioned a are always a go to when I visit here.
Excellent drinks

I really can't say enough to praise Sable. I've been here a few times over the past two years, and every visit is tops. The bar and wait staff are all incredibly friendly, knowledgeable, and receptive. Griffin is an excellent bartender who will make you the perfect drink whether you know what you want, or not. Can't recommend enough.
Oh my god my son just said he couldn't ask for a better meal. The impossible burger is possibly the most delicious veggie burger ever. Service is great ambience is fantastic. Yummy scale - amazing.
Outstanding cocktail program with enthusiastic and friendly bartenders. Shame you can’t buy them a drink. The Jell-O shots are a must try.

Very nice spot.  The staff were incredibly nice and friendly.  We sat at the bar for cocktails.  The cocktails were all clever, although they were not cheap, they definitely earned their prices, especially in this neighborhood.  Very glad to have randomly stopped in here. The setting Is nice generally, but the bar felt really comfortable relative to many of the other busy busy bars in the neighborhood
Was bit pricey for breakfast but was nice.
Acai bowl! Don't forget that. The best thing on the menu. We also get chicken and salmon salad so delicious
Great brunch and cheap mimosas!
I loved my lox scrambled eggs and steak frites! Best brunch!
Great coctails with awesome views! Good area
Uninspired decor and staff. Not empowered to make customers happy. Low energy. But when your manager sits at the end of the bar micromanaging....what would one epwct?

Terrific brunch with a great vibe and music playing. Attentive service and great food. The highlight of this place is their tremendous selection of bourbon, single malt scotch, and other spirits. I took a picture of the very hard to find Blackadder, one of the best single malts in the world (in my opinion). Highly recommend this place for that reason and yeah the food and service is top notch.

I use to come here when my boss lived near by.  Her and the rest of the gang would order drinks, which they loved, and I would stuff my face with their appetizers.  At one point, i believe they had bacon wrapped dates.  I would get a double order of those.
Enjoyed atmosphere.
Delicious. And our server Robert was the absolute best. It's a bit out of the way from work for a lunch, but I will be back VERY soon.
They had really good food. I enjoyed the Sable Burger. Very filling! Yum!
They have breakfast there
Fantastic....
Bone apple teeth
Really good breakfast. Worth a visit
Great place for brunch. Amazing menu.
Excellent food, great service and friendly staff. Atmosphere is perfect for girls night or date night. Dessert gets 5 stars!

Food was very good.  My husband had the 2 egg breakfast. I had the fried egg sandwich.  The potatoes were so yummy. Small quaint little place.  There is a mix of booths, couches,  and higher table with bench plush seats on one side and individuals chairs on the other.  Very clean,  good service.  We had an issue with our order being lost for a moment in the mix of things but the staff came out and was honest about what happened and offered compensation. They even sent us on our way with some yummy popcorn. The same menu is offered in room if you are staying at the Palomar. Nice job Sable!

This is a great place for food, drinks, and for a casual hang out spot. The bartender was very knowledgeable and provided great service. Also, the bar has a very extensive menu of alcohol including bourbon and whiskey. When you order a straight drink they leave the bottle right next to your glass as an added touch.
Food here is really good.
Great breakfast, lovely Mimosa and Bloody Mary, fun staff!
One of the best cocktail spots in river north!  Always have unique drinks that change with the season.  We always go here before big dinners and we are never disappointed.
Really great bartender helped us pick the perfect cocktails for us both and treated us to 2 fancy jello shots for my fiances 30th birthday!
The french fries are amazing! Drinks were good... Service as well. A cozy little place!
Great hotel restaurant, good attentive staff. Well knowledged in craft cocktails. 11/10
Worst dirty martini ever... Staff talked with themselves no engagement with the customers...

Have long loved sable but our recent visit left something to be desired. Think they're trying to mix it up a bit with different focus but the food isn't quite as tasty, nor the menu that appealing.  House burger was pretty good along with chocolate/coffee dessert. Gnudi not so good. Burrata and ham toast yummy and generous portion. I do miss the cheese curds.
Went here for the Christmas decor and it didn't disappoint. The holiday drinks and mugs were fantastic
Great holiday spot

Came in here for a quick breakfast before we went out about our day. The soft scramble with Lox was perfect. The soft scramble isn't easy to do well and this was done quite well. as you can see from the photos, we also enjoyed some scotch early on in the day and they have a wonderful selection to choose from.  While this is a hotel bar, I did not get that feeling at all. More felt like a comfortable locals bar where I might find myself after work or before headed out on the town. The bartender was friendly, knowledgeable and inviting.
Fun holiday drinks and food!
Great lunch

Came in for the holiday decorations but they weren’t good enough to distract me from the horrible service.  Sat at a table in the bar and no server came to the table. Watched as they cleared 3 tables and served two others around us without ever stopping by. Had to go to bar to get my own drinks for the table.
Great food with great service! Definitely recommend.
The ‘miracle’ Christmas bar is fun, the drinks are good, and the wait staff is excellent!
Great drinks, food, and service. 💯
Great drinks, really good food, excellent staff and cool vibe.  Busy!
Great Burger, excelent mixology.

Our party had a horrible experience this Sunday morning. We called in advance to make sure that the kitchen was open this weekend and were told it would be. After traveling to this location for breakfast we arrived and were greeted with a very loud group of hotel staff on strike and a closed restaurant. I had already read all the bad reviews and should have listened, but wanted to give this place the benefit of the doubt.
I wish the staff was as good as the bourbon selection. It's my favorite place for bargain priced top-shelf bourbon but some of the bartenders could be better.

One of the best bars in all of Chicago.  A 23-year Chicago resident, I happily stumbled upon Sable by accident while walking to Navy Pier one weekend and stood there gazing at the array of whisk(e)y bottles on display.  Not only do they have an impressive selection of whiskies, their cocktail list is quite spectacular too and their food is outstanding.  Sable is far more than your average hotel bar (Hotel Palomar) - it stands mightily on its own.  Well worth a visit - I try to come by every time I'm back in Chicago.
Incredible Cat!! :)
Good cocktail spot in River North
The drinks are always delicious!
Excellent drink selection, well informed bartenders, decent pricing

Went here with a friend. Had a couple delicious cocktails, salmon, and mussels. The salmon was great, seasoned well, cooked juicy. Mussels were doing the most with the chorizo, cream sauce and other bits and bobs.  Danny was a great bar tender. Accommodating and explained items well. Mellow atmosphere close to our hotel. Would recommend.
Best cocktails ever . I been here like 4 times . All of the drinks are amazing.
Sable has some of the best cocktails in the city. Great vibes and knowledgeable bartenders. Food is good too.

A single malt connoisseur's dream come true. They have a separate book just for single malts. They clinching factor for me was the japanese whiskeys. Most place don't carry those, and sables has all years. Truly amazing! If you are into single malts, there cannot be a better place.
As mentioned by other reviews, prices are steep. I just paid $14 for a Moscow mule.
Great drink list!!
Great bar
Great cocktails.
A very reasonable bar considering its location and interiors
Unique drink menu with fun shareable plates. Can't ask for much more, especially in nice weather out on the patio.
Great service (Allie was excellent) and decent veg food
Awesome mixed drinks and great bartenders.
Great, friendly service. Excellent brunch.
Best drinks in the city! I love ending the night with a drink at Sable!
The food is great, but the cocktails are amazing. I hit this spot every time I am in Chicago.

Bespoke cocktails tantalize in this dimly lit bar.  The staff, drinks, and nibbles are excellent.  Don't like what you see on the cocktail list? No problem.  Tell the mixologist your likes/dislikes and s/he will make sure you leave happy!

It was a decent spot. Server was amazing and very friendly. Their butterscotch pudding was very good. I did. Otherwise, I did not feel other items.that I tried stood out so much. I wouldn't mind going there again but it not be something that would prefer. It's worth trying at least once, you might find something that you like better there.
Absolutely
Great drinks an craft cocktails. Very good food as well. Good location
Excellent drink menu with highend rare bourbons which were reasonably priced. Not too loud. Danny was very helpfull and friendly.

I met a friend here for drinks on Sunday this past weekend, while I was in town for a conference. When I walked in, the place was pretty empty, not unusual for a Sunday. I sat down at the bar and talked to the bartender briefly about their drink list. I had absolutely no idea how extensive the list was. There is an entire page for gin & tonics. They have classic cocktails with a twist, and their "unforgettable" cocktails. The bartender had only been working there for a few months but he had the entire list memorized. After my friend got there, she told me it was on of the best cocktail bars in the city and she had always wanted to go. The waitress was so funny and quirky. She also had so many recommendations and was very knowledgeable on the drinks. When she was busy at other tables, what I can assume was the manager would swing by our table and ask how our drinks were. He was suggest other drinks based on our taste preferences, and assured us if we hated it he would send it back and try something new. It was such a nice surprise for being in downtown Chicago. I would go back again in a heartbeat.
Beer list is lacking.  Large selection of cocktails.  A little on the pricey side.  Overall this is an ok spot to grab a cocktail.
Excellent cocktails. Food is very good as well.

My husband and I came in for a nightcap and were treated like VIPs. A nice gentlemen named Joey helped us decide what to drink.  (The menu is huge!) When my husband had given his drink a try but didn't care too much for the taste, Joey chatted with him and figured out something else he would like and then brought us that without charging us for the first drink. He was super friendly and suggested other great places to go in the city.  Delicious drinks! Highly recommend!
Best pancakes I've ever had! Since its also the kitchen for the Palomar Hotel, wish the menu had more variety.
Good place for drinks, but not so much for food.

Unknowledgeable staff about their food. Claims like beef from California is juicer, and the bacon bits on the deviled eggs are pancetta. Pretentious serving of non-alcoholic beverages in mini bottles. Tried deviled eggs - hands down worst ever. Egg whites hard as a rock, filling liquid/runny with extreme vinegar flavor, topped with “pancetta” aka bacon bits. They get a two star rating because setting is nice if you want to sit at the bar with a date and drink. Drinks look pretty.
Great spot for a drink. Staff is extremely friendly and and drink menu is endless. Great vibe.
Awesome drinks!
Terrific late night atmosphere and staff.
Fantastic selection cocktails very well prepared. Staff seem very happy to work there and this helps creates a great atmosphere.
Great cocktails. Friendly staff. Great for a date!
Over priced, poor quality ingredients prepared poorly
Great service! Must try their gin and tonic! Spanish style! Went there by myself and felt really comfortable!
A good place to grab some nice drinks with friends. Upscale, not too loud, and the staff are super friendly - our waiter gave us the recipe for a drink my friend loved.

Good place to go to for a date. Remember to make a reservation before you go though since it can get crowded. Good thing is that it's not loud.  They have an extensive cocktail menu and  it can be exhausting to read them all. I had the war of the roses, good if you like sweet drinks with a bit of an edge to them.  We tried the tuna small plate, and you literally get 2 little pieces of tuna- well made and taste great, but not really vfm.  We also tried the pasta special, hand cut rigatoni with pumpkin sauce. This was really good, and enough to share with a second person.  The place itself looks like the lobby for the hotel. It has some seating in the back, and living room-like space in the front. They have bar seating as well. Place definitely looks chic, while it does have a tv, it's not a beer and sports place at all.
Extremely Rude host.
Trying to be pretentious, but it's not working. This used to be a favorite spot, but now apparently a reserved table on Open Table doesn't mean you have a TABLE - only "space", whatever that means.

Very cool bar area. Plenty of scotchy scotch for the enthusiasts. My buddies ordered some drinks and plates to share. The deviled eggs were okay, a bit salty and too pricey. The short rib sliders were good, well prepared and tender. The chicken thighs with a concord grape gastrique was solid but the gastrique needed a little bit more acidity. The pork belly was okay. Service was amazing. She was very friendly and warm.
This place does not serve creme brûlée! (Especially after midnight) we waited all night for this late night creme brûlée. Lies, Google
I felt it was bit expensive but good drinks
Excellent cocktails and wonderful service.
Wonderful whiskey based drink list.

I have heard good things about Sable and I'm glad I finally got to try. Well-made cocktails, with interesting twists on the classics. We didn't try food but I loved the menu with an option to "Get the whole menu". ;) We stopped by late on a Saturday evening after Norah Jones concert and I was a little surprised by how loud and crowded it was - but hey, there was a bachelorette party going on so can't be too hard on them. But I would love to come back on a weeknight to try some of their other cocktails without worrying about someone spilling drinks on me.
Great bartenders
Great drinks and appetizers!
We went for drinks at the bar. I had a fig cocktail that actually tasted like figs. It was nice. The bartenders were nice.
Great atmosphere.  Craft cocktails.
They ran out of hamburgers (really?), the drinks were deplorable, and the food... not good at all.

Just get the pretzel bites. Seriously sick of these overpriced ridiculous lounges. The cocktails were sub par sometimes simple works best. If youre going to make these exasperated drinks they better be good. Service was great though.

Cocktails are amazing here, there's a very cool speakeasy vibe to the decor and the drink menu. I was a bit disappointed in the food, just a bunch of overpriced small plates without much flavor, I was very glad I wasn't the one footing the bill.

Great atmosphere. Some of the most tasty, and creative cocktails in Chicago. Bartenders are on top of their mixology game and they can personally craft a cocktail just for you if you simply tell them what flavor profile and spirit you enjoy most. The food is pretty good but their cocktails are much better! For a perfect craft cocktail I highly recommend!
Food was really good.

Just stopped in for a quick after dinner drink. The atmosphere in this place is amazing. Everything is classy and well though out. It is dark but not too dark where you bump your knees on everything. I just got a beer on tap but I hear their specialty cocktails (especially their whiskey ones) are amazing. They are pricy at $14 a piece. I didn't try any of the food but from what I saw waiters carrying by me the whole time I was there and from what my friends have told me, it's worth checking out.
Great drinks, solid food.  Waiter was extremely knowledgeable and helpful.
The limited menu makes each dish unique and delicious. Bar staff is knowledgeable and professional. Perfect spot after a long day.

Very pleased. This Paleo girl got exactly what she needed.   They pack food in containers and you pay by the ounce like you do in a deli.  I got some of the best carnitas, ever.  Tender and juicy.  Good flavor.  And good chunky guacamole.  I hate watery guacamole with a passion and Azteca's was the way it should be, lot's lime and chunks.  Cashier and the gal in the kitchen were both VERY nice and happy to help.
Came for drinks, stuffy and over priced.
New Executive Chef very refined new menu.  Seamless and warm hearted front of the house.  Great imagination behind the drinks as well.  Very memorable experience!
Great cocktails.
Bartenders really know their stuff. Great craft cocktails, and bartenders can tailor the drink based on guest's tastes. Always happy with the food and service
Very good bar and great eats
Excellent innovative cocktails and food
Wonderful cocktails. Amazing appitizers - tacos and wagyu sliders. Can't wait to visit again.
Great place for some late night drinks
I eat here all of the time because my summer diet is just rosé and calamari. The service is very good here as well as having great food.
Gets very crowded, but the drinks are good and food is more than decent.
Food is ok.. Nothing memorable ... Visited and had the ceviche, steak tartare, calamari and a couple of deserts try outs... Bar area is a busy while the dining area provides calmer seating...
Went for brunch, very interesting menu, every item seemed to have a twist. All of the food was fresh and service was very attentive.

Do you love creative and original craft cocktails? Then stop reading this and get to Sable! They have some of the best drinks in the city. I hear the food is great but I don't let it distract me from the fabulous drinks. There are often beautiful people here too which doesn't hurt.
I have travelled a bit. Probably the best upper class bar i have been in. Ever. Great selection of drinks and interesting tasty food options, including vegetarian.

Fantastic cocktails and usually a good but not overcrowded bar scene. All the food that I've had has been great, although the oysters were poorly shucked. Bartenders are super friendly and informative as the concoct those perfectly made drinks. A more sophisticated scene than others in the immediate area.
A great environment for a relaxing night out
Amazing atmosphere. Waiting and hosting staff is fantastic and really know their stuff! As for the food and drinks.... OUTSTANDING. Will 100% be returning for more!
Good cocktails, as always... but the food portions have gotten ridiculously small, as have the wine pours.
Decent food, but the service was lacking and prices were high for what we ordered.
Great cocktails!
The cocktails are absolutely amazing
The Blazed & Infused is the most complex cocktail I'll drink in 2016 (slight hyperbole). Cold comfort was also fantastic.
Staying here and decided to have a late night bite when I got in.  Awesome food. Chill atmosphere.
The drinks and food are great.  I recommend the Elective Amnesia cocktail.   You'll get a buzz after a few sips.
Love the whisky cocktails , food is okay

Restaurant is located inside the Hotel Palomar and easily accessible. Bar area was packed and a bit overcrowded considering the small width of the overall bar. In the back they have a beautiful dining area. I called ahead for a party of 6 so they seated us in a very nice room in back.  Overall food was extremely overrated in my opinion. I did enjoy the cheese curds which came with a spicy ketchup and offered a very unique flavor but lets face it you don't go to a place like this looking for cheese curds.  Unfortunately the Venison and the Octopus were both taken off the menu which was a bit disappointing.  The scallops were a bit too salty but fairly large. The drink menu offers a plentiful variety of drinks... I chose to try the bourbon flight and will admit it was OUTSTANDING and one of the few reasons I still gave this place a 3 star.  The restaurant manager was a nice guy and did send us some champagne and a free desert on the house as well as an order of Turkey Poutine (the Turkey Poutine was a bit awkward as most of our diners were vegetarian and I told him that upfront). The toffee cake is very delicious and worth trying!  Overall I recommend coming here for the drinks and not the food! Not a bad option for a drink after work or a weekend evening but far from what we expected!
We went for just cocktails.  The best ones we had in Chicago.  Fantastic fresh originals, and all the classics well made.  The drinks will not dissapoint.
awesome cocktails great liqour selection, I could live at the bar
Great food, drinks, and atmosphere.  To eat we got the lamb, scallops, and capicola flatbread which were all delicious.  The War of Roses was also a great drink.
Recently had drinks here.  The bartender was great, really knowledgeable on the drinks.  The drinks were delicious and the drink menu was huge!
Good food. Odd atmosphere. Our service was so-so. I think there are better alternatives
Awesome!

The food here is pretty mediocre. I was disappointed with every dish I ordered, and I even had to send one back because it was inedible. The service was fine and the drinks were pretty good, but I would not go back. I did email the manager about my experience and they responded very politely and apologized and even offered a free dinner should I choose to return which was very unexpected. However, I still haven't returned for my free dinner so... I think that says it all.

One of my favorite places for cocktails in river north.  Friendly staff and talented mixologists.  Great food.  Half and full size portions.  Excellent for sharing.  Flatbreads are delicious.  Truffle fries are to die for.  The dark chocolate souffle with peanut butter and salty caramel ice cream is divine.  Perfect ending.
Great drinks and awesome comfort food
Delicious food and some of the best cocktails I've had in Chicago

Brunch at Sable may have impressed my small town Michigan family but it did not impress my Chicago pallet. Everything on the menu sounded amazing but at a half win loose ratio I'm rounding down.  I thought we could just walk in 20min before our 9:45am reservation with no problem, but apparently people make reservations at 8am!? They did apologize for the wait and offered us coffee, even though we were early, 1 point Sable.  We were right next to the kitchen so its hard to not have good service but our waiter was very helpful and peppy.  I got a caffeine buzz just from a cup of coffee being poured next to me. The fresh squeezed orange juice is good but the portion size is huge, like 500 calories (estimate) huge, but clearly I couldn't waste any!  As instructed we shared all dishes family style, half portion between 4:  Pull Apart Butterscotch Monkey Bread 7, couldn't hold a flame to my grandmothers. Too much bread, not enough butterscotch goodness.  House Cured Salmon Gravlox: pickled red onions, pumpernickel 10, loved by my Swedish grandmother, and everyone else. The thick dill shmear really made this dish for me as I'm not a salmon fan.  Maine Lobster Frittata: potatoes, chives, corn, oven dried tomatoes 11, was good but too many potatoes. Here's a hint $11 for a hockey puck sized frittata shouldn't have any fillers, like potatoes. Lacked that sparkle for me, but enjoyed by my less judgey family.  Espresso-Cocoa Nib Steak & Eggs: farm eggs, steak, hash browns 15, was definitely a winner. The steak was super tender and flavorful and a very good sized portion.  Three Sister's Grits with White Cheddar 4 were delicious and comforting and the same size porting as all of the entrees! Definitely recommend adding a side of these!  We ate light and didn't have booze, our check was around $72 for 4. I would be up for trying dinner but I won't be back for brunch, too many other places to try!

Sable offers options for small or standard plates for most of the menu items, which is nice. The food I had was really good, but there were a few things on the menu that they were out of or had 86ed. Unfortunately, those items were the ones I wanted to try the most. The drink menu was decent but not outstanding, and our waiter was very friendly. There is also a good amount of outdoor seating.

The food is excellent the wait staff superb my fiancee and I were looking for somewhere to unwind after a long work week and there we went worth every dime an our waiter neal courteous friendly just a cool dude me an my future wife have found our unwind spot recommend all to try it

What a flavorful menu, each dish is small (if you take the 1/2 portion) but an explosion of flavors, the ambience is loud but not overwhelmingly so, the service is outstanding and attentive.  One more comment, pair your drinks carefully with your meals, they have it, you just have to be ready to select it.

Mezcal and Sympathy  Well, maybe not sympathy, but you get the idea. I tried Sable, a new hotel bar a few weeks ago with a friend who loves Mezcal as much as I do. Mezcal and other intriguing liquors are served in a chic, yet approachable manner. Go for the original, classically-inspired cocktails and stay for the food: delightful deviled quail eggs, yummy fried Smelt, and more!  Perfect for a business lunch, happy hour, or a dinner date.

This place is listed on one of the Top 20 Chicago cocktail spots for good reason, but what nobody mentioned was the amazing food.  I went and got the chicken & waffles as was SO impressed.  Very tender chicken, an amazingly soft & sweet belgian waffle and this bourbon infused pure maple syrup that makes you want to drink it by itself as a dessert.  It's one of the best chicken & waffle dished that I've had.  As for the bar area, it's a well-laid out lounge-next-to-bar kind of feel and the cocktails do not disappoint.  The wait staff is very knowledgeable and will not lead you wrong.  It's just really good.
Incredible service. Make sure you order half serves and try lots of foods. Too many cocktails to count. The Truffle Butter Burgers are awesome.
Always tasty breakfast for dinner.
(Translated by Google) Here you can taste modern and atypical American cuisine. Recommend!  (Original) Здесь можно отведать современную и нетипичную для америки американскую кухню. Рекомендую!

I usually avoid hotel bars and restaurants but I really like Sable. With the exception of Watershed in the basement of Pops for Champagne, Sable is one of the few places in the Mag Mile/east River North neighborhood where you can order a great cocktail. Helmed by Top Chef cheftestant Heather Terhune (whose mean demeanor made me cringe through season nine), the menu is a modern take on comfort food and American classics and pairs well with the complex cocktails. My favorite bites have been the mini-lobster rolls, short rib sliders and fried chicken and waffles.

We came here for my Birthday Breakfast and after looking over the menu, I decided to go with my breakfast favorite, Eggs Benedict. Our waitress was really nice. I asked her to have my hash browns crispy and she said, "That is how we make them!" I was like perfect, maybe my birthday is turning around right now. My wife ordered a egg white veggie scramble that came with fresh fruit. She asked if I would split the order of Applewood Bacon with her. Honestly does she need to ask me? We're talking Bacon here! Adding Bacon to anything is a simple YES! Now the more I thought about this I thought sharing or splitting Bacon just isn't right but I decided to honor my side of the agreement. Trust me I was thinking about how to get all the bacon though. Don't judge me because it is my birthday!  The Eggs Benedict were good. There were simple and traditional but that is what I wanted. I did not want a crazy chef inspired version of Eggs Benedict. This totally hit the spot on my birthday. Now the star of the show was the Hash Browns. These things were amazing and one of the best Hash Browns I have ever had in the city. There are other restaurants in the City that only make Hash Browns and they make the worse Hash Browns I have ever had. I won't name them but I think you can figure out who they are. They only really make Hash Browns. I think the Sable should change there name to: We make VERY DELICIOUS Hash Browns! I would go to a place named that.  In fact, the Hash Brown were so good I even had to Tweet about them. I was even lucky enough to receive a response from the Chef Heather Terhune. I thought that was really sweet of her. In fact, she has promised to email me the recipe for my birthday. How nice is that? We spoke a few times and she had to cut down the recipe for me from 50 servings to 3 servings. Thanks so much Chef! This is turning out to be a great birthday so far.  My wife loved here breakfast. It was perfect for her. It had everything she loves for breakfast: egg whites, veggies and fresh fruit. She gave me a taste and it was really good. She was a little let down with the bacon. When she hears Applewood Bacon she is expecting a thick cut of bacon and this was not very thick cut. So I can see her complaint. For me it is hard to say no to any piece of bacon and I had no problem cleaning up the bacon.  This was a great place for breakfast.  Also a shout out to Chef Heather Terhune and thanks for the recipe. I need more Hash Browns...you have me hooked and thanks for making my day special. I truly appreciate it.
The drinks here are great. There is one less than helpful female bartender, but the rest more than make up for her. The food is spectacular and well presented. Highly Recomment!
It's a nice looking spot, but the mixology-style drinks are just boring.  They don't add any style or precision to them.  Fine for river north area.

Went here with a foodie co-worker last month and have been back once already. Ingredients are sourced locally and/or sustainably and the food is served in small or large portions made for sharing. My favorite is the shrimp and grits, but everything else I had was delicious too. Muscles, Fried chicken and waffles, Barley Risotto. The bar has a handful of good craft beers to pair with the meal as well as wine and full bar.

I cannot say enough great things about this restaurant. I've never met a menu item I didn't love. The service is exceptional and someone is always there to provide the best experience possible. Our server Cristian offered up his favorite menu items and I couldn't have been happier that we took him up on his suggestions. I was there for brunch and had the tamale, literally mind blowing. He answered all our questions honestly and throughouly, which I really appreciated. He clearly cared about making our dining experience a great one and his passion shined through his service. Might I mention they have green charteuse on tap. Amazing, everything was amazing. Can't wait to go back!

My wife and I decided to check out Sable based on Opentable and Yelp reviews.  Let me just say that the reviews were pretty much spot on!  The food was delicious and well portioned.  We shared the Poutine, Short Rib Sliders, Bacon Jam and Chicken and waffles.  Our server, Rachel was fantastic in helping my wife pick out a wine and she made great recommendations on the food.  She was very informative, extremely generous and decidedly very laid back.  She did not make us feel rushed in choosing and made us feel as though we were her only table.  Overall, this was one of the best experiences for us, dining in Chicago.  A true gem!

I've been to this restaurant a handful of times. The menu changes enough that it feels never with every visit. The menu is eclectic, but could have more menu options. The food is delicious and I like the use of local ingredients.

An overall excellent meal highlighted by great food, an extensive cocktail menu, and spot on service. Highlights of my experience were the sweet, delicate,  perfectly seasoned and executed sea scallops; the NY strip steak; short rib sliders, and sweet corn creme brulee.
friendly, accommodating service when we had a large party. the corn brulee was amazing. definitely recommend coming here for some great food.
Nice place, nice athmosphere A little pricey for food, but the drinks are amazing. They have hand crafted drinks, the service is excellent. i recoomend this place.
Entrees are decent but mixed drinks are less than great. Save your time and head to another 5 star Chicago restaurant.
Good food and atmosphere, but prices are steep and the portions are minute.

Food was ultra - get the bacon jam, the flatbread and the steak. Super long queue at the restaurant though so we got a bar seat after 15min. Service was ok. Restaurant and hotel looks super cool. Also the cocktails are great - I got one of the refreshing ones and it was!
Food was delicious. Huge drink menu! Terribly slow service.

Good place to grab a drink and appetizers after work. Had the Kentucky Grazer with bourbon, Pimms, lemon, bitters, and mint - a unique cocktail with lots of flavor. Food was outstanding - I'd recommend the pork belly sliders and the Moroccan spiced almonds and cashews.

I like Sable, but definitely not for the food. The cocktail menu is ominous, but if you get some help from the staff they will point you in the right direction, and possibly off the menu altogether. Go for the cocktails, but don't stay for the food...
Great food paired with a massive cocktail list and friendly service = great spot! Don't be intimidated by the drink list, the servers or bar tenders are happy to guide you!
The cocktails are amazing and the bartender's level of service and expertise worth the visit.

Loved the idea of American tapas. I think the bacon jam was my favorite dish but everything was really good. The Indian dish was even really good (and I'm Indian) even though the menu was mostly American. Would definitely take someone back here,

Sable has execellent food.  I've been here for lunch several times, and it's always superb.  Their drinks are interesting (think: rosemary infused, etc).  The service is good however it's also a little slow during the peak time frame.  This is located in the Palomer  hotel.

This place has awesome drinks!! I have never eaten here but the staff ar tge bar is wonderful. They are able to recommend drinks for you if they are not on the menu and will cutomize to your needs! Looking forward to eating there

A restaurant so tasty and beloved that I named my cat after it. Seriously, I named my cat Sable because of this place.  It was love at first bite - all thanks to Baconfest 2011 and a dish so tasty, we had to go to the restaurant to experience it ourselves. Heather's bacon jam is out of this world. Wether you get it smothered on cheddar scallion scones at brunch or on the crisp, buttery baguette at dinner, you can't go wrong.  My all time favorites besides the bacon jam are the corn creme brule, veal meatballs and the fried green tomatoes. Every time I go back, I fall in love with a new dish.  Go with a group of 4 so you can sample lots of dishes. Upscale comfort food with a twist, tapas style... what's not to love?!

(Translated by Google) Excellent food. We had ordered several small dishes, the whole reminds a bit of the tapas style. Service was very friendly. Good wine list. We also had an excellent American breakfast.  (Original) Exzellentes Essen. Wir hatten mehrere kleine Gerichte bestellt, das ganze erinnert etwas an den Tapas Style. Bedienung war sehr freundlich. Gute Weinkarte. Ebenfalls hatten wir auch schon ein exzellentes American Frühstück.

Outstanding!!!!!  Great happening restaurant, trendy yet elegant. The variety of dishes is amazing at Sable. The sweet corn crème brulee was awesome at its taste and had a good wine list too. Will surly visit Sable once again as early as possible :):)
Love me some fancy cocktails. I highly recommend the point taken. Cheers!

Amazing cocktail list and really chic gastro-pub/lounge. I love Sable's kitchy cocktail names, but best of all they make their drinks with locally sourced ingredients and they mix old classics with contemporary.  The whole place has a '40's feel but the menu is modern and is great for all occasions.  I love coming here for afterwork drinks and bar bites - they have everything from homemade beef jerky, Wisconsin cheese curds, and lots of great bacony dishes! I love the bacon jam on a baguette and the bacon wrapped dates and all of their flatbreads, especially the pork belly and apple.  Chef Heather may look familiar to you if you watched Bravo's Top Chef!

Located in a hotel, this is anything but a hotel restaurant. This Top Chef contestent run restaurant overs a variety of rich food.  Come with a big appetite and wallet. This is a good place to take out of towers or go for a special occasion. #30daychallenge   #chicago

Sable is a great place for good ol' fashion American cuisine. Heather the executive chef  ( whom I was on Top Chef Texas with) makes the food very approachable and delicious. They have booths and open tables so it's great for a friends night out or a date night. Some of my favorites here are the short rib sliders, deviled eggs, and the sweet corn creme brulee. Not to mention that Heather was also a pastry chef for a long time so she kills it with the desserts, they are all so good it's hard to pick a favorite. Behind the bar leading the crew is Mike Ryan ( a former Moto employee) his flavor profile and ability to construct drinks is almost unmatched in the city. He has a great personality and a awesome haircut. The staff is all very personable and you get treat very nicely. If I am able to sneak out early one night from work, this would be on my list of places to stop at before I make it home.
Cocktails were poorly measured and incoherent
Another great small plates spot in Chicago. Cocktail menu from top-notch mixologists is a must try as well. Crowded after work but not too packed or noisy to enjoy yourself. Bacon jam is a MUST.
Had a great lunch at Sable - they have delicious salads. Their grilled cheese sandwich selection is fantastic. And a great bar as well!

hated it.  food comes out immediately so obviously not made to order. too many flavors in every dish that don't go together. Lamb Burger gamey with feta and aioli to nauseating effect. rushed service. expensive
Went to Sable prepared to hate it because of the executive chef's poor attitude on Top Chef. However, the food was lovely and the service was pretty good. I would go back.
Fantastic food - try the lamb burger!
Outstanding. In the Palomar Hotel. Unique local...check it out for the most amazing drink  list ever. Try the cloak and dagger or the Pegu club.
